KCNA Blasts Japan's Sinister Moves to Scuttle Six-party Talks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The six-party talks for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula are now underway in Beijing as already reported.
 Many countries of the world have expressed sympathy with the principled stand of the DPRK to fundamentally settle the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. and hoped the talks would prove fruitful substantially conducive to the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan, however, is swimming against such trend of the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is well proved by the remarks made by its Chief Cabinet Secretary Shiozaki. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When interviewed on Feb. 5 he said it goes without saying that the "abduction issue" is very important for Japan and there can be no normalization of the relations between the two countries unless the "abduction issue" is settled. As if it were not enough with this, he went the lengths of blustering that Japan can not but assert this issue at the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not hard to guess how Japan will approach the talks and what attitude it will take at the talks, judging from such reckless remarks made by a guy who professes to be a spokesman for the Japanese government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Explicitly speaking, the six-party talks are aimed, in name and reality, at solving the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula and pending issues between the U.S. and the DPRK related to it, in view of their motive, origin, purport and purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Japan, however, used to vitiate the atmosphere of the talks by persistently raising the "abduction issue" completely irrelevant to the major agenda of the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, China Youth News on Sept. 1, 2003 when the six-party talks have just kicked off published an article titled "The key issue of the six-party talks is the nuclear issue but Japan proposed the 'abduction issue' as a main one" in which it contended that "The scrutiny into how the talks proceeded makes it clear that Japan raised the 'abduction issue' to the DPRK, considering it as the major task of the talks, thus creating greater difficulties in the way of the six-party talks." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is ridiculous and disgusting, indeed, for Japan to assert that the "abduction issue" should be a main issue to be discussed at the talks and the like though it is not qualified to participate in the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present reality goes to clearly prove that Japan is not only least interested in the settlement of the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula but is deliberately working hard to hamstring the work of the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What matters is why the politicians of Japan are so persistently trying to induce the six-party talks to take up the "abduction issue." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In a word, the Abe government is also keen to use the "abduction issue" as a pretext for evading Japan's responsibility for redressing its past crimes as the preceding regimes did and stir up national chauvinism and bitterness towards the DPRK among its people in a bid to consolidate its political foundation to stay in power unchallenged through the election to the House of Councillors slated to take place in July. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their behavior cannot be construed otherwise than a mean political mode of political dwarfs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK does not care whether the Abe Cabinet stirs up scrambles among different parties and factions to stay in power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But it can never overlook any act of inciting confrontation with the DPRK with a hue and cry over the "abduction issue" and trying to use it for staying in power though it had already found its solution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international community will never tolerate the moves of the politicians of this insular country if the six-party talks remain complicated and fail to produce substantial results due to its wrong doings.

S. Korean CBS's False Report on DPRK Refuted  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland gave the following answer to a question put by KCNA Friday over the false report about the DPRK released by the south Korean CBS:
 The CBS reported recently that the authorities of the north are now all out to arrest "prisoners" whom it claimed succeeded in a group escape from a detention center in Hwasong County, North Hamgyong Province late last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Explicitly speaking, it is a sheer lie and fabrication. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not the first time that it released such false reports on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and the right-wing conservative forces in south Korea are working with bloodshot eyes to tarnish the image of the DPRK which is wining victory after victory. Their anti-DPRK smear campaign has become all the more undisguised since its successful nuclear test, in particular. The south Korean conservative media are also joining in this campaign, spreading all kinds of misinformation. The recent false propaganda was part of the campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a matter of fact, the DPRK's prestige has risen to its zenith and the public inside and outside Korea has become more vocal in supporting and praising its Songun policy since its access to nukes. The anti-DPRK smear campaign more desperately intensified by the U.S. and the south Korean ultra-right conservative forces is, therefore, nothing but a foolish move to stem this trend and destabilize it, much upset by the above-said development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has increased outlay for anti-DPRK psychological warfare from a budget for this year and its State Department blustered that it would drastically increase budget for "Voice of America" and "Voice of Free Asia" in a bid to step up the "democratization of the north through radio broadcasting." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities, too, are joining the U.S. and the "Grand National Party" in their anti-DPRK smear campaign by increasing the relevant budget and intensifying psychological offensive, talking about "aid to north Korean defectors" and "improvement of human rights record in the north." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such dastardly farce will get them nowhere but only touch off bitterer indignation among all the Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said south Korean media should stop such shameful act as working as a trumpeter in the anti-DPRK smear campaign launched by anti-reunification forces. The CBS should apologize for its false report on the DPRK and take a measure against the recurrence of any similar case. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and the ultra-right conservatives in south Korea should stop such foolish and clumsy farce, bearing deep in mind that their evermore desperate anti-DPRK smear campaign would only bring their despicable colors into bolder relief and adversely affect the nation's efforts for the detente on the Korean Peninsula and the improvement of the inter-Korean relations. They will be held wholly accountable for all the ensuing consequences.

Cambodian Party Leader on Relations with DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- We are sure that the traditional relations of friendship between the Funcinpec Party of Cambodia and the Workers' Party of Korea, the Cambodian people and the Korean people would continue to develop on good terms in the future, too, Keoputh Rasmey, chairman of the Funcinpec Party, said this when meeting Choe Han Chun, DPRK ambassador to Cambodia, who paid a farewell call on him on Feb. 2.
  He said that the long-standing relations of friendship between the Cambodian and the Korean peoples provided by Great King Norodom Sihanouk and President Kim Il Sung have developed amid the interest of the peoples of the two countries over the last several decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The support and encouragement extended by Kim Il Sung to Norodom Sihanouk in his efforts to achieve the cause of national reconciliation and peace in Cambodia is recognized not only by the Cambodian people but by other peoples of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We praise the Korean people for having heroically stood up against the arbitrary practices of the U.S. imperialists, single-mindedly united under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, and hope that peace will be preserved on the Korean Peninsula in their fundamental interest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Funcinpec Party and the royal government of Cambodia will always support the just policy of the WPK and the DPRK government to defend the sovereignty of the country and achieve reunification.

Reception Given by Syrian Charge d'Affaires A.I. 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- Muhammad Adib Al Hani, charge d'affaires ad interim of the Syrian embassy here, gave a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on Thursday on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il.
 Present on invitation were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The charge d'affaires a.i. in a speech at the reception said that the Korean people have made great successes in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Bashar Al-Assad and Kim Jong Il have exerted positive efforts to boost the bilateral relations, he said, stressing that these relations will grow stronger this year, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking next, Choe Thae Bok said that the friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and Syria provided by President Kim Il Sung and Hafez Al-Assad, the eternal leader of the Syrian people, are growing from strength to strength as the days go by under the special care of Kim Jong Il and Bashar Al-Assad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are extending full support and solidarity to the Syrian people in their struggle to find a fair and comprehensive solution to the Mideast issue under the leadership of the Baath Arab Socialist Party headed by Bashar Al-Assad, he said, adding that the Korean people will strive hard to boost the relations with Syria in all fields.

Kim Jong Il's Songun Revolutionary Leadership Feats Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- A national seminar on the undying Songun revolutionary leadership feats performed by Kim Jong Il was held at the People's Palace of Culture on Thursday.
 Six papers were presented there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Candidate Academician, Prof. and Dr. Thae Hyong Chol, president of the Academy of Social Sciences, said that Kim Jong Il propounded the idea of building a great prosperous powerful nation on the basis of the great exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung in the nation-building and defined the revolutionary principle of Songun which calls for relying on the People's Army and its revolutionary spirit as the fundamental principle for building a great prosperous powerful nation, thus indicating the basic ways to dynamically push forward the building of the above-said nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Editor-in-Chief of Rodong Sinmun Kim Jung Hyop noted that Kim Jong Il has developed in depth the Juche-based Songun idea and, on this basis, put the work for equipping the whole Party and society with this idea on a higher stage. He added that Kim Jong Il has trained the People's Army as armed forces defending the leader and an ideologically strong army and achieved the unity of the army and the people in idea and spirit and work style, thus realizing the great army-people unity in the DPRK something unprecedented in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prof. and Dr. Han Hung Song, vice-president of the Political University of the Ministry of People's Security, said that Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il has performed undying feats by building an invincible military power equipped with strong war deterrent. He proved these exploits lie in that Kim Jong Il has built the People's Army into the strongest army and enabled the DPRK to attain the status of a nuclear weapons state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prof. and Dr. Pak Son Ho, president of University of National Economics, pointed out that Kim Jong Il, with a profound insight into the requirement for accomplishing the cause of socialism and the specific conditions of the DPRK, laid it down as the strategic line of economic construction in the Songun era to give priority to the development of the national defence industry and, at the same time, develop the light industry and agriculture simultaneously and provided his dynamic on-the-spot guidance to various domains of the national economy, thereby bringing about a great leap forward and innovations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prof. and Dr. Ri Jong Hyok, director of the National Reunification Institute, referred to the fact that Kim Jong Il clearly indicated the orientation and ways of accomplishing the cause of national reunification as early as possible, firmly united all the Koreans, guided by the idea of "By our nation itself" and powerfully aroused them to the reunification movement, thus opening an epochal phase for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Kwang Yon, chief secretary of the Party Committee of the Secretariat of the Cabinet, stressed that the struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation is difficult and complicated but the army and people of the DPRK can pull through any difficulties and ordeals and certainly build a rich and powerful country on this land as long as there is the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the seminar were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials of party and administrative bodies and working people's organizations at the national institutions and in Pyongyang and officials of educational and scientific institutions, Party cadre training institutions and fields of literature and art, media and in the field of preserving revolutionary relics.

Joint Student Actions for Settlement of Issue of Registration Fee in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- Students from across south Korea reportedly waged a joint struggle to settle the issue of the registration fee on Feb. 2.
 A ceremony of inaugurating the "National Students Measure Committee for Education" was held in Seoul on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the ceremony accused the political camp of refusing to take any measure in this respect though the hike of the registration fee has long presented itself as a social problem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the ceremony at least 500 students staged the first joint action of students across south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants at a meeting held in front of the Myongdong Cathedral declared that they would stage the second joint action on March 30, adding that three million students would struggle in unity for the settlement of the educational issue.

Stop to Expansion of U.S. Military Base Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The All-People Measure Committee for Checking the Expansion of the U.S. Military Base in Phyongthaek, the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and other civic and public organizations in south Korea reportedly held a press conference in front of the building of the "Ministry of National Defense" on Feb. 2 and demanded a stop to the illegal moves to expand the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek.
 The press release read out at the press conference recalled the recent disclosure of the outburst of the commander of the U.S. forces in south Korea made on Jan. 18 that 50 percent of the defense burden share was needed for the transfer of the U.S. Second Division to Phyongthaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This means that the cost of the relocation of the U.S. Second Division which is to be borne by the U.S. will be covered out of the budget of the south Korean "government," it said, branding the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek as illegal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It bitterly denounced the sycophantic and treacherous act of the "government" to pay the relocation cost under the name of the share of the burden for the upkeep of the U.S. forces by deceiving the people.

Kimjongilia Exhibition Opens at Ministry of People's Armed Forces
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The Kimjongilia Exhibition of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces opened on Thursday to celebrate February 16.
 Displayed there are beautiful Kimjongilias grown by soldiers of the Korean People's Army with boundless reverence and best wishes for Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The officials and employees of the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Greenhouse of the ministry, officials, teachers and students and employees of Kim Il Sung Political University and the April 25 House of Culture have brought the undying flowers into full bloom with all sincerity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials, soldiers and employees of various units and squads including the Pak Myong Hun's unit and the Jong Yun Ho's squad under the ministry turned out as one in growing the flowers of the sun and put the red flowers on show.

Celebrations Held in India and Switzerland
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- Celebration meetings were held in India and Switzerland on Feb. 3 on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il.
 On display at the venues of the meetings were photos showing undying exploits of the peerlessly great men. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vishwanath, director-general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, informed the meeting of a decision of the "International Kim Il Sung Prize" Council to award the prize to Kim Jong Il on his birthday and referred to the fact that he is making immortal contributions to world peace and security and accomplishment of the human cause of independence with his unique Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harish Gupta, secretary general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, expressed the belief that the Korean people would build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and surely reunify the country under the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 P. Shiv Shankar, chairman of the Indian National Preparatory Committee for Commemorating the Day of the Sun and February 16, highly praised the exploits of Kim Jong Il in his Songun leadership, noting that he is victoriously leading the Korean people with Songun politics based on the Juche idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Martin Lotscher, chairman of the Swiss Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, said Kim Jong Il is a great statesman, thinker and theoretician and outstanding strategist making imperishable contributions to the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings.

End to U.S. Forces' Presence in S. Korea Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The Korean nation can no longer allow the U.S. imperialist aggression forces' presence in south Korea to continue and now is the time for it to put a definite end to the criminal Korea policy of the U.S., says Rodong Sinmun Friday in a signed article.
 Stressing that it is an unavoidable demand of the times and national history, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The occupation of south Korea by the U.S. imperialist forces is a direct product of the U.S. Korea policy of domination and aggression. The U.S. ambition of this nature finds intensive manifestation in its desperate obstruction to the reunification of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. will be left with no pretext to stay in south Korea when the north and the south of Korea get reconciled and united and achieve national reunification. The U.S. does not want this. It is for this reason that whenever there crops up an atmosphere of reconciliation and unity between the north and the south the U.S. chills it either by faking up a shocking case or by inciting confrontation and war hysteria through war exercises and thus leading the situation to the extreme pitch of strain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation is craving for peace and reunification of the country so earnestly and making painstaking efforts to achieve them only to suffer a failure, running up against an ordeal and snag in every step. The U.S. is to blame for this. The Korean nation will continue to come across stumbling blocks and impasse in its way to reunification as long as the U.S. occupation of south Korea and its moves to keep Korea divided continue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pullback of the U.S. troops from south Korea is also what is strongly demanded by the south Koreans themselves, who have experienced all sorts of national disgrace and misfortune generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A prompt end must be put to the history of the U.S. occupation of south Korea and the policy of dominating Korea pursued by it which has persistently hindered Korea's reunification, seriously violated peace on this land and inflicted bitter pain and death upon the south Koreans after dividing the Korean Peninsula into the north and the south.

SOFA Branded as Slavery Document of Modern Version
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the North Headquarters of the Nationwide Special Committee for Probing the Truth behind the GIs' Crimes issued a statement Thursday on the lapse of 40 years since the U.S.-south Korea "Status of Forces Agreement" (SOFA) took effect.
 The SOFA faked up by the pro-U.S. flunkeyist traitors under the U.S. pressure is a slavery document of modern version which legalizes the U.S. forces' occupation of south Korea and guarantees the GIs' crimes by law, the statement says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The long list of crimes including murder, assaults and looting committed by soldiers of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces over the past four decades run into more than 100,000 cases. However, none of them was punished by law, but they are riding high and mighty on their high horses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is national shame and tragedy that such unequal document as SOFA still remains in south Korea although the world has entered the 21st century. The south Korean people should launch into a vehement struggle to get all the humiliating "agreements" and "treaties" signed with the U.S. scrapped and drive the U.S. imperialist aggression forces, the root cause of misfortune and disasters, out of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And they should bring the sledgehammer down on the heads of the traitors to the nation like the cohorts of the Grand National Party of south Korea who have left indelible disgrace on the nation, bringing unspeakable misfortunes and pains to the people, after reducing south Korea to a land where GIs boss it around by forging the treacherous SOFA.

Consumer Goods Production Increases
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The working people of the light industrial factories throughout the country have turned out in the efforts to implement the call of the joint New Year editorial for decisively improving the production of consumer goods.
 The light-industry and the local-industry factories are increasing the variety and quality of consumer goods by tapping to the maximum the latent reserves and potentials in order to supply more consumer goods to the people this year meeting significant holidays. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ryongsong Disabled Soldiers' Injection Boots Factory, the Pyongyang Hosiery Factory and the Songyo Knitted Goods Factory in Pyongyang are considerably boosting their production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar successes have been reported from the light industrial factories in North Phyongan Province which have closely combined production with science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the Pakchon Silk Mill the blanket production process of which has been put on modern footing is mass-producing blankets of various patterns to suit the living customs and feelings of the Korean people and the Sinuiju Cosmetic Factory functional cosmetics to delight the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Sinuiju Shoes Factory and the Sinuiju Enamel Ware Factory turn out fashionable and quality shoes and snow-white enamel vessels to satisfy the growing demand for the products. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The workers of the Hamhung Disabled Soldiers' Plastic Daily Necessities Factory are manufacturing various kinds of raincoats including raincoat and rainjacket while striving to extend the assortment of goods. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The newly reconstructed essential foodstuff factories in Pyongyang, Kanggye, Haeju, Pukchang and other parts are making large quantities of tasty and nutritive soy sauce and bean paste for the improvement of the people's dietary life.

New Schoolchildren's Palace under Construction in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The construction of a schoolchildren's palace is progressing apace in Phyongsong City, South Phyongan Province.
 The palace, a Korean-style building, will have a theatre, gymnasium, swimming pool, various circle rooms and training rooms and be furnished with adequate welfare service facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are a hundred and scores of schoolchildren's palaces and halls across the country where the children are regarded as king. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last year witnessed the completion of the reconstruction of the Samjiyon Schoolchildren's Palace on an expansion basis on the occasion of the February 16, the birthday of Kim Jong Il.

Repeal of S. Korea-U.S. SOFA Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front made public a statement on Thursday 40 years after the unequal south Korea-U.S. "Status of Forces Agreement" (SOFA) took effect, according to the Internet site "Kuguk Jonson."
 The statement says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The SOFA, which was concluded in July of 1966 by the U.S. and pro-U.S. sycophantic traitors in south Korea and took effect on February 9, 1967, is a slavery document of modern version which legalizes the U.S. military occupation of south Korea and gives Yankee murderers unlimited privilege of extraterritorial rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a shame of our people and national tragedy that there exists such traitorous document as SOFA even in the 21st century when the people are aspiring after independence, the June 15 era of reunification in which all the Korean people are pooling their efforts to achieve reunification of the country.  The people from all walks of life should more dynamically conduct the struggle to get the humiliating SOFA repealed and drive the U.S. imperialist aggressor troops out of south Korea. For the present, they should intensify the mass struggles against the U.S. in different parts of south Korea, including the struggle against the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should also vigorously wage the struggle to eliminate the pro-American conservative forces including the "Grand National Party" who seek to grab power and let the U.S. imperialist aggressor troops stay in south Korea forever, bringing all disgrace and misfortune to the Korean people.

S. Korean People's Actions against FTA Supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea extends full support and encouragement to the people from all walks of life across south Korea in their recent strong actions against the conclusion of the south Korea-U.S. "Free Trade Agreement" (FTA), considering them as the most righteous and just patriotic ones for the sovereignty and vital rights of the Korean nation.
 A spokesman for its Central Committee says this in a statement Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The FTA the U.S. is pressurizing south Korea to sign is nothing but an "agreement" and document inviting a national ruin and treachery as it is aimed at deepening the former's domination and subjugation of the latter and putting the living of peasants and other people to destitution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The reality goes to prove that the U.S. is the most brazen-faced aggressor and plunderer in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement calls upon the south Korean farmers to more dynamically conduct the patriotic actions against the U.S. pressure for negotiations and its moves for domination and interference and not to tolerate under any circumstances such pro-U.S. sycophantic acts of the traitors including the Grand National Party of south Korea as bartering away the dignity and interests of the nation to serve the U.S.

Kim Jong Il dirige la Planta Hidroelectrica No. 1 de Orangchon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 9 de febrero (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, dirigio sobre el terreno la Planta Hidroelectrica No. 1 de Orangchon y el Criadero de Peces del lago Jangyon, construidos nuevamente.
  Ante todo, el Dirigente hizo una visita de orientacion sobre la planta electrica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recorrer las cabinas de generador electrico y de distribucion de electricidad, hizo conocimientos detallados del estado de construccion y de produccion electrica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta central hidroelectrica, que produce gran cantidad de electricidad con el agua de Orangchon, esta disenada racionalmente y se construyo en un alto nivel cualitativo, dijo y se mostro muy satisfecho de esta moderna obra terminada por los habitantes de la provincia de Hamgyong del Norte. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Senalo que vale la pena jactarnos de esta magnifica planta edificada por los constructores aun en el periodo de serias dificultades economicas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Es el mejor metodo conveniente al principio de rentabilidad el hecho de que se inauguro con anticipacion esta planta hidroelectrica para elevar la eficiencia de inversion en la misma, apunto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente indico las tareas que se presentan en la administracion de la planta y la utilizacion eficiente de la electricidad producida aqui. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Acto seguido, el Dirigente recorrio el campo de construccion del dique de Orangchon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al ver el gigante dique que crece alto atravesando la hondonada, se entero de la marcha de esta obra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Destaco que los miembros de la brigada juvenil y otros constructores deben seguir dando acicate a su trabajo con el mismo impetu con que construyeron en un corto tiempo la planta hidroelectrica no. 1 para terminar anticipadamente lo restante de la obra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los ultimos anos, aun bajo dificiles condiciones, hemos construido por doquier numerosas plantas de gran potencia registrando un subito crecimiento en la generacion electrica, recordo y apunto que este orgulloso cambio comprueba la justeza y vitalidad de la politica del PTC consistente en construir en gran medida las plantas hidroelectricas de mediano y pequeno tamanos junto con las de gran dimension. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para cubrir en lo suficiente la demanda de energia electrica que crece bruscamente en dicha provincia, hay que lograr el maximo rendimiento de las plantas existentes y, al mismo tiempo, construir mas centrales hidroelectricas al buscar y explotar todos los recursos hidraulicos latentes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente dirigio luego el Criadero de Peces del lago Jangyon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recorrer varios lugares incluyendo el estanque de cria y la sala de incubacion, hizo conocimiento detallado de la crianza de peces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente presento las tareas programaticas que sirven de guia para desplegarla ampliamente como movimiento masivo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante su orientacion sobre la provincia, el Dirigente indico las tareas que se presentan para elevar a un nivel mas alto la gestion economica de la misma. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En esta provincia hay muchas empresas de ramas claves de la economia nacional, a saber, de la industria metalurgica y la extractiva y, por eso, ocupa un lugar muy importante en el desarrollo economico del pais, recalco e instruyo que esta localidad debe jugar el rol de vanguardia en la construccion de una potencia economica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le acompanaron el secretario responsable del Comite del PTC en la provincia de Hamgyong del Norte, Hong Sok Hyong, el secretario y el jefe de departamento del CC del PTC, Kim Ki Nam y Pak Nam Gi, respectivamente.

Kim Jong Il dirige fabrica de alimentos basicos y central Kunmin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 9 de febrero (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, dirigio sobre el terreno la Fabrica de Alimentos Basicos de Chongjin y la recien construida Central Hidroelectrica Kunmin. 
  Ante todo, el Dirigente visito la Fabrica de Alimentos Basicos de Chongjin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se dio cuenta del estado de reconstruccion y produccion recorriendo los procesos productivos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al ver diversos alimentos basicos producidos a granel que avienen al paladar del pueblo coreano, se puso muy contento de esta magnifica planta que contribuiria enormemente a la vida alimentaria del pueblo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Senalo la necesidad de normalizar la produccion en un alto nivel para hacer aporte substancial a la vida del pueblo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los ultimos anos, se han construido muchas fabricas modernas de alimentos basicos que aportan grandes beneficios, recordo y dijo que cuando se pongan en pleno funcionamiento las fabricas ya construidas y termine la construccion planificada de las plantas similares, se registrara un viraje trascendental en la vida alimentaria del pueblo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   La clave para normalizar la produccion de alimentos basicos es resolver satisfactoriamente el problema de materias primas, indico y subrayo que para este fin, se debe organizar minuciosamente la creacion de firmes bases de materias primas en las granjas cooperativas, producirlas y suministrarlas a tiempo motivando el entusiasmo de los granjeros. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Subrayo que es importante elevar la calidad de los alimentos basicos, porque son inseparables de la vida del pueblo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Hay que profundizar la investigacion sobre esta rama, asegurar la unificacion de indices tecnicos y realizar en un nivel alto la automatizacion de procesos productivos, concluyo.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Luego, el Dirigente dirigio sobre el terreno la nueva Central Hidroelectrica Kunmin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras escuchar las explicaciones ante el panorama de la planta, recorrio los compartimientos de generadores electricos y de distribucion electrica y otros varios lugares cerciorandose en detalles del estado de construccion y generacion electrica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Muy contento de esta moderna planta construida magnificamente a tono de la epoca del Songun, senalo que el termino de esta obra en un corto plazo es un fruto valioso de la infinita fidelidad a la revolucion y del ardiente patriotismo de los constructores y los ayudantes voluntarios y evaluo de altos sus meritos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Subrayo la necesidad de mejorar la administracion tecnica y de equipos para poner la planta en pleno funcionamiento e indico las tareas que surgen para el respecto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le acompanaron Hong Sok Hyong, secretario responsable del comite del PTC en la Provincia de Hamgyong del Norte, Kim Ki Nam y Pak Nam Gi, secretario y jefe de departamento del CC del PTC, respectivamente.
